result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob S McGeshick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License(3rd+ w/in3Yrs), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must obtain his GED/HSED.

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
The defendant may not consume or possess alcohol and no entry into any taverns or bars.
The defendant is eligible for expunction upon successful completion of probation under 973.015.

The defendant must take all medications as prescribed and in the manner in which they are prescribed by a treating physician.

The defendant must submit a DNA sample.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jacob S McGeshick in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:05 AM. State - resolved. Scholke - 15CF13 - plead G to counts #1, #3, #9 and #13 as alleged, remainder DRI, 15CF101 - plead G to both counts as alleged, on 15CF13 - #1, #9, and #13 and count #2 on 15CF101 - place on probation for 3 years with with conditions of: $500 fine on #1, $500 fine on count #9, $500 fine on #13, costs and fees on all other counts plead to, AODA, absolute sobriety, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, employment, 100 hours of community service, take all meds as prescribed, $655.00 restitution for buy money, #3 - 6 months in jail - 31 days credit, #1 on 15CF101 - 6 months in jail - consecutive to count #1 - 28 days credit on that count. State agrees but makes one clarification that the $655.00 restitution should be a cost for drug buy money and is to be paid at no less than $100.00/month. State moves to dismiss and read in counts #2, #4, #5, #6, #7, #8, #10, #11, #12, #14 and #15 on 15CF13. Court dismisses and reads in those counts. Defendant pleads G to counts #1, #3, #9 and #13 as alleged on 15CF13 and pleads G to counts #1 and #2 on 15CF101 as alleged. Court has plea qusetionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constititional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Scholke makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - asks for expungement. McGeshick makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 15CF13 - counts #1, #9 and #13 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, maintain absolute sobriety, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 100 hours of community service, take all meds as prescribed and only in the manner in which they are prescribed, $655.00 cost for drug buy money - to be paid at $100.00/month after release from custody - paid thru probation, obtain HSED, #1 - $500 fine plus costs - paid thru probation, #9 - $500.00 fine plus costs - paid thru probation, count #13 - $500.00 fine plus costs - paid thru probation; count #2 on 15CF101 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years, concurrent to 15CF13, with same conditions except no additional community service; count #3 on 15CF13 - 6 months in FC jail - good time and huber allowed - 31 days credit - report no later than 8:00 AM on 4/27/16, count #2 on 15CF101 - 6 months in FC jail - consecutive to count #3 on 15CF13 - huber and good time allowed - 28 days credit, costs only on both of those counts - take bond posted and remainder of bond posted can go on 15CF13, submit DNA sample with expungement rights given, will allow expungement upon successful completion of probation under 973.015, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, right to appeal, adjourned.
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 18, 2016 at 09:00 am.
